 the game will be better off for it.<br>
<br>
I have had the balance arguments before with monks &amp; was always met with, &quot;don't nerf monks  ...oh, and warriors are fine where they are.&quot;  There was a problem, and something did need to be done about it.  Despite appearances, I never like seeing any class nerfed.  The armageddon attitude of monks here and elsewhere, however, has risen to comical levels.  The best suggestion that I can make to monks is to cut the drama &amp; start making rational objective arguments with some unbiased backing data.  These constant threats of massive account cancellations only make you look like selfish children who can't have their own way.  Do yourselves a favor &amp; try to achieve some objectivity instead of just having a tantrum and throwing around some biased data.  It's the dramatists making threats &amp; exaggerationg the consequences that earn the jibes from warriors such as myself.  <br>
<br>
Take a step back &amp; look at some of these threads from the outside.  Surely you can see how infantile some of the monks on this board are acting.<br>
<br>
