<br>
If the few posts with post-patch data are correct, VI apparently has made it more difficult for monks in the 1100 ac range, while not touching the 1400+ ac monks at all.  Maybe this is a mob-specific change, but if not they didn't begin to address the problem at all.  <br>
<br>
I'm sure you're aware of this, but telling a roomful of angry people to &lt;stop whining/quit throwing tantrums/settle down&gt; rarely has any good effect.  You are, after all, browsing the monk board.  Feel free to take a break from browsing until we have some concrete data (barring VI changes, probably in a day or so we should have some).  Sarcasm may be a justified response to melodrama, but it draws in people like myself to defend my class.<br>
<br>
I didn't start a twinked iksar, I leveled myself to 45 pre-Kunark with such uber gear as my bare fists, wu's gauntlets (yay lightstone effect), gator legs, and froggie crown.  I had to stay under 14 lbs, so i couldn't loot FS.  I've deleted/given away plat to stay underweight.  In short, try to remember that there are some of us here who have been around for a long time, through the ups and the downs.  Hearken back to the days of Kunark, when warriors essentially did monk damage, while still tanking the best with or without defensive.  It would have been easier to nerf warriors, but instead they put monks on a different offense table and gave us better weapons.<br>
<br>
A word on mudflation:<br>
In this particular case, mudflation is utterly irrelevant.  The problem is the nature of the best gear for monks, not how much of it enters the game.  If VI had a linear progression for gear, there would be no problem.  <br>
<br>
1)  Draw up a set of uber gear for various classes<br>
2)  Compare them to see if they make different classes too close together.<br>
<br>
Or, what's even simpler, work out a plan for &lt;insert class here&gt; by item slot, stating expansion-specific maximums for stat increases.  Tada!  Problem solved.<br>
<br>
I do resent the fact that items I will never get and people I will never meet have indirectly caused <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> my</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> ability to take damage to be decreased, regardless of the amount of the decrease.  Is this whining?  /shrug it's a fairly subjective term. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=291578"><IMG SRC="http://lyndar.netfirms.com/sigpic.JPG" ALIGN=center></a><BR>Grandmaster<BR>Bristlebane</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showPrevMessage?topicID=317.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showNextMessage?topicID=317.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=317.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.emailToFriend?topicID=317.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.threadControl?topicID=317.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=317.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=317.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td col